Software Engineer 
            You will join the Research & Development team and will have the opportunity to contribute to building next-generation industrial security products. If you enjoy a challenging yet flexible work environment, don’t miss this opportunity to join Nozomi Networks.
Location: Mendrisio, Switzerland
Requirements
            Skills

Knowledge and experience with Agile methodologies, TDD, Continuous Integration & Delivery
High degree of flexibility and willingness to take-on new project and challenges
Enthusiastic about working as part of an exciting startup company

                      
           Programming Languages

Javascript & WebGL
Experience with computer graphics technologies (OpenGL, DirectX, WebGL, Software rendering, etc)
Experience with computer graphics technologies (OpenGL, DirectX, WebGL, Software rendering, etc)
Knowledge of Ruby and C++ are a plus

Languages
English (must)
German/Swiss German (plus)
Italian (plus)
French (plus)


Years of experience:  5+
How To Apply: To apply, please send your CV to careers@nozominetworks.com






Pre-Sales Engineer / Technical Consultant (EUROPE)
            We are looking for motivated candidates to join our System Engineering Team and be part of an exciting startup.
Location: Mendrisio, Switzerland
Key responsibilities of the Systems Engineer (SE)

Support partners and customers during pre-sales, sales and post-sales activities.
Work closely with our Sales team, qualify sales opportunities from a technical perspective, present solutions, gather customer requirements and design the architecture to include in quotations.
Act as a technical focal point in managing communications with partners, to deliver the right messages and to receive the feedback from the field.
Follow up with customers for resolution of issues or new feature requests, interacting internally with the Research and Development Team as needed.

“Must haves” of the SE

7+ years of experience working in customer-facing roles as a Security Consultant, System Integrator or System Engineer
Strong knowledge of information security principles
Good understanding of complex networks, protocols and networking technologies
Good communication (written and verbal) and presentation skills
Good problem finding and solving skills
Dedicated to achieving goals
Strong work ethic
Good written and spoken English proficiency
Availability and willingness to travel

“Nice to haves” of the SE

Bachelor’s Degree (or equivalent) in computer systems or telecommunications
Experience in the field of ICS (Industrial Control Systems) security projects
Security certifications (i.e. CISSP, CISA, CISM, GICSP,  ISA99 Cybersecurity, IACRB Certified SCADA Security Architect, ISO27001 Lead Auditor)
Knowledge of a second language (German or French desired)

How to Apply: To apply, please send your CV to careers@nozominetworks.com





Pre-Sales Engineer / Technical Consultant (North America)
            We are looking for motivated candidates to join our System Engineering Team and be part of an exciting startup.
Location: North America, US
Key responsibilities of the Systems Engineer (SE)

Support partners and customers during pre-sales, sales and post-sales activities.
Work closely with our Sales team, qualify sales opportunities from a technical perspective, present solutions, gather customer requirements and design the architecture to include in quotations.
Act as a technical focal point in managing communications with partners, to deliver the right messages and to receive the feedback from the field.
Follow up with customers for resolution of issues or new feature requests, interacting internally with the Research and Development Team as needed.

“Must haves” of the SE

7+ years of experience working in customer-facing roles as a Security Consultant, System Integrator or System Engineer
Strong knowledge of information security principles
Good understanding of complex networks, protocols and networking technologies
Good communication (written and verbal) and presentation skills
Good problem finding and solving skills
Dedicated to achieving goals
Strong work ethic
Good written and spoken English proficiency
Availability and willingness to travel

“Nice to haves” of the SE

Bachelor’s Degree (or equivalent) in computer systems or telecommunications
Experience in the field of ICS (Industrial Control Systems) security projects
Security certifications (i.e. CISSP, CISA, CISM, GICSP,  ISA99 Cybersecurity, IACRB Certified SCADA Security Architect, ISO27001 Lead Auditor)
Knowledge of a second language (German or French desired)

How to Apply: To apply, please send your CV to careers@nozominetworks.com




 Sr. Director, Sales
            We are looking for motivated candidates to join our Sales Team in a leadership position and be part of an exciting startup.
Location: North America, US
Key responsibilities

New business development through leveraging your network and qualifying leads.
Secure key reference accounts in relevant verticals
Execute land-and-expand campaigns, from POC to large deployments
Deliver successfully on enterprise quota targets

“Must haves” of the Sales Leader

Industrial focus: Oil & Gas, Power Generation, Energy Utilities
Experience in selling Network Security products, and comfortable working in startups
10+ years of Direct Sales experience, ideally selling to industrial automation, industrial controls, and/or industrial security customers

How to Apply: To apply, please send your CV to careers@nozominetworks.com




 Director, Demand Generation
            We are looking for motivated candidates to join our Marketing Team in a leadership position and be part of an exciting startup.  Ideal role for a great Demand Generation professional looking to take his/her career to the next level.
Location: Silicon Valley, US
Key responsibilities

Define and manage the execution of B2B digital marketing programs that drive awareness, engagement and pipeline. Leverage all digital and direct marketing tactics to drive top-of-funnel and downstream conversion metrics.
Create and manage the systems and processes for campaign planning, initiation, development and launch.  Prepares outbound sales performance reports by collecting, analyzing, and summarizing data and trends.
Identify and evaluate state-of-the-art technologies; define user requirements; establish technical specifications, productivity and customer service standards.  Versed in Salesforce.com, Marketo, Hootsuite, and other sales/marketing solutions.
Must be able to master inbound and outbound call strategies. We are looking for someone who leads by example and works tirelessly alongside Sales to drive revenue via sales enablement campaigns and activity.  

“Must haves” of the Demand Generation leader

5+ years of experience with a focus overseeing lead generation and customer acquisition activities, marketing events, lead nurture & development, marketing operations, marketing metrics & web analytics
Inbound, data-driven, digital marketer with a history of integrating content marketing and demand generation strategies to increase revenue
Experience with Industrial OR Security products is a Nice-To-Have, but not required.
Must be driven, smart, self-initiated, a hustler, ambitious, able to work with distributed/remote teams, comfortable in startup environments, and confident.

How to Apply: To apply, please send your CV to careers@nozominetworks.com














































 



