press release


					June 14, 2017, 1:50 p.m. EDT
				
Nozomi Networks Named a 2017 Gartner Cool Vendor
Recognition from world's leading research and advisory firm comes as the company announces strong customer growth and strategic hires



























SAN FRANCISCO, Jun 14, 2017 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE via COMTEX) --


                                        

Nozomi Networks, Inc
., the pioneer in real-time cybersecurity and operational visibility for industrial control systems (ICS), today announced that it has been selected by Gartner, Inc., as a 2017 Cool Vendor*. Cool Vendor reports identify companies who are recognized for their innovation, impact and intrigue in the markets they serve.        









"It's an honor for us to be a Gartner Cool Vendor. We are proud of our innovation and its positive impact on our global customers," said Nozomi Networks CEO Edgard Capdevielle. "We believe this is strong validation of the strength of our product and its proven value to customers around the globe. Our employees are gratified to see Nozomi Networks recognized by Gartner and know technology executives and boards can rely on Gartner for valuable insights."


                                        








Leveraging artificial intelligence and machine learning, Nozomi Networks has created a single platform for comprehensive ICS cybersecurity with tens of thousands of industrial devices secured around the world. It combines anomaly detection, vulnerability assessment and asset inventory into one solution that secures critical infrastructure operations amid rising global threats.


                                        








In addition to the Gartner news, the company         today announced
 it has added Global Chief Marketing Officer Kim Legelis and Vice President of Business Development Chet Namboodri to the company's management team. Both bring deep experience and valuable business relationships in industrial networking and ICS security forged during their previous tenures with Cisco Systems, GE, Lockheed Martin, Industrial Defender and Symantec.


                                        








Since announcing a         $7.5 million series A funding
 round in October, Nozomi Networks has seen better than expected market growth in both North America and Europe. In March Nozomi Networks announced a         new release of SCADAguardian
, delivering the industry's most comprehensive solution for both operational visibility and ICS cybersecurity. The company exceeded its Q1 forecast for customer growth, strengthened key partnerships with         Fortinet
 and         Check Point
 and expanded its overall partner program to more than a dozen integrators. The company has deployed its technologies globally to leaders in key industries such as oil, power generation, nuclear energy and manufacturing. Beyond customer expansion, industry accolades continue to accumulate. Nozomi Networks was recognized at the RSA Conference as Cyber Defense Magazine's         Cutting Edge ICS/SCADA Security Solution Winner
. The company won the popular vote in this year's         Cybersecurity Excellence Awards
; and just last week Nozomi Networks was named a         Red Herring Top 100 North America Finalist
.


                                        








"When we moved corporate headquarters to San Francisco and added Edgard (Capdevielle) to the team in October we expected it to be a solid year for Nozomi Networks," said Co-founder and Chief Product Officer Andrea Carcano. "The progress we've made so far has exceeded our expectations. I believe this latest recognition from Gartner, as well as significant customer growth and the industry talent joining our team, is a testament to the strength of our company, our product and our vision; and an indicator of much more to come in the months ahead."


                                        








About Nozomi NetworksNozomi Networks is revolutionizing Industrial Control System (ICS) cybersecurity with the most comprehensive platform to deliver real-time cybersecurity and operational visibility. Since 2013 the company has innovated the use of machine learning and artificial intelligence to meet the unique challenges of critical infrastructure operations. Nozomi Networks delivers both cybersecurity and process anomaly detection along with industrial network visualization and monitoring, asset inventory, and vulnerability assessment. Deployed in the world's largest industrial installations, customers benefit from enhanced cybersecurity and improved operational reliability with one end-to-end solution. Nozomi Networks is headquartered in San Francisco, California.          www.nozominetworks.com









Gartner DisclaimerGartner does not endorse any vendor, product or service depicted in our research publications, and does not advise technology users to select only those vendors with the highest ratings or other designation.  Gartner research publications consist of the opinions of Gartner's research organization and should not be construed as statements of fact.  Gartner disclaims all warranties, expressed or implied, with respect to this research, including any warranties of merchantability or fitness for a particular purpose.


                                        








*        Gartner Cool Vendors in Endpoint, Mobile, Network and Gateway Security, 2017
, Published: 08 June 2017 ID: G00326807, Analyst(s): John Girard | Lawrence Orans | Ruggero Contu | Manjunath Bhat | Dionisio Zumerle


                                        








